Great resources for anyone who is new to Oracle Cloud

Overall this was a great use of time and money. I can now converse intelligently on any facet of OCI, though not in great depth. This is probably best understood by people who already have a technical base - understand concepts of networking, storage, security, containers, cloud. Though Rohit does not assume it. 

Strengths of the Course: 
 * Expertise - The class is written presented by a Senior Director.  He knows the product well. Delivery is clear (no verbal stumbles, hestitation). 
 * Breadth -  It seems to covers all of the functions / features of OCI at the right  technical level, not too high or too low
 * Timelessness - It typically avoids specifying details that will likely change over time (eg. price per CPU etc) 
 * Lack of Spin - Oracle is typically hugely biased/ lots of spin. This course largely avoids that
 * Grouping - Information is grouped, References other courses to find more detailed information. 
*  Clear diagrams with animation to explain

Weakness of the Course: 
* About half of the quiz questions cover information not explicitly covered in the videos. 
   You can make a good guess at it, and the explanation of right/wrong answers if excellent. I learned 
   alot from the quizzes - the questions do target the most important information
* Some Spin - We are the cheapest (10x cheaper than other services). 
* Would like summary sheets of the information presented for each topic, links to evergreen Oracle docs
